---
import SiteHead from '../components/SiteHead.astro';
import SharedCSS from '../components/SharedCSS.astro';
import SiteNav from '../components/SiteNav.astro';
---
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <SiteHead title="Privacy Policy — ArgusRecruit" description="How ArgusRecruit collects, uses, and protects your personal information." lang="en" />
  <SharedCSS />
  <style>
    .legal { max-width: 820px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 140px 32px 90px; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.85); line-height: 1.75; }
    .legal h1 { font-family: 'Space Grotesk',sans-serif; font-size: clamp(32px,4vw,48px); font-weight: 500; letter-spacing: -1px; text-transform: uppercase; line-height: 1.1; margin-bottom: 16px; }
    .legal .meta { color: var(--primary-gold); font-size: 12px; letter-spacing: 2.5px; text-transform: uppercase; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 36px; }
    .legal h2 { font-family: 'Space Grotesk',sans-serif; font-size: 22px; font-weight: 500; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.5px; color: #fff; margin-top: 42px; margin-bottom: 14px; }
    .legal p { margin-bottom: 16px; font-size: 15.5px; }
    .legal ul { margin: 14px 0 18px 22px; }
    .legal li { margin-bottom: 8px; }
    .legal a { color: var(--primary-gold); }
    @media (max-width: 560px) { .legal { padding: 120px 20px 70px; } }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <SiteNav lang="en" pathInLang="/privacy/" />

  <main class="legal">
    <div class="meta">Legal</div>
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>

    <p>This Privacy Policy explains how ArgusRecruit ("we", "us", "our") collects, uses, and protects your personal information when you visit argusrecruit.com or interact with our executive search services. We operate from Yerevan, Armenia, and serve clients and candidates worldwide.</p>

    <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
    <p>We collect information you provide directly to us, including:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Name, email address, phone number, and LinkedIn profile when you apply to a role or contact us</li>
      <li>CVs, cover notes, and other application materials you choose to submit</li>
      <li>Company name, role requirements, and contact details when you hire us as a client</li>
      <li>Email address when you subscribe to job alerts</li>
    </ul>
    <p>We also collect limited technical data automatically: IP address, browser type, pages visited, and approximate location for security and analytics purposes.</p>

    <h2>2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>To evaluate your candidacy for open roles and present qualified candidates to our clients</li>
      <li>To contact you about opportunities that match your background — now or in the future</li>
      <li>To deliver job alerts you have subscribed to (you can unsubscribe at any time)</li>
      <li>To respond to your inquiries and provide our search services</li>
      <li>To comply with legal obligations and protect against fraud</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>3. Sharing Your Information</h2>
    <p>Candidate information is shared with prospective employers only with your explicit consent and only in connection with a specific role you have applied for or expressed interest in. We do not sell your personal data.</p>
    <p>We may share information with trusted service providers (email delivery, hosting, analytics) under confidentiality obligations, and where required by law.</p>

    <h2>4. Data Retention</h2>
    <p>We retain candidate records for as long as is useful for matching you with future roles, or until you ask us to delete them. Client records are retained for the duration of our engagement plus the period required by accounting and tax law.</p>

    <h2>5. Your Rights</h2>
    <p>You have the right to access, correct, or delete your personal data, and to object to or restrict certain uses. To exercise these rights, email <a href="mailto:contact@argusrecruit.com">contact@argusrecruit.com</a> from the address on file.</p>

    <h2>6. Security</h2>
    <p>We use industry-standard safeguards to protect your information, including encrypted transport (HTTPS), restricted access, and reputable third-party processors. No method of transmission over the internet is 100% secure, but we work hard to keep your data safe.</p>

    <h2>7. International Transfers</h2>
    <p>Because we work across multiple time zones and jurisdictions, your information may be processed in countries other than your own, including Armenia, the European Union, and the United States. Where required, we put contractual safeguards in place.</p>

    <h2>8. Cookies</h2>
    <p>Our website uses minimal cookies for functionality and analytics. You can disable cookies in your browser settings without significantly affecting your experience on this site.</p>

    <h2>9. Children</h2>
    <p>Our services are intended for adults. We do not knowingly collect information from anyone under 18.</p>

    <h2>10. Changes to This Policy</h2>
    <p>We may update this policy from time to time. The "Last updated" date at the top of this page will always reflect the most recent revision. Significant changes will be communicated to active subscribers and candidates by email.</p>

    <h2>11. Contact</h2>
    <p>Questions about this policy or your data: <a href="mailto:contact@argusrecruit.com">contact@argusrecruit.com</a><br />
    ArgusRecruit · Yerevan, Armenia</p>

    <p style="margin-top: 36px; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.55); font-size: 13px;">Last updated: 23 May 2026</p>
  </main>

  <footer>© 2026 ArgusRecruit · <a href="/">Home</a></footer>
</body>
</html>
